**1.1 "Licensor"** shall mean Jax Wolf (JAXW01F), the sole author and rights holder.

**1.2 "Materials"** shall mean all source code, documentation, frameworks,
methodologies, mathematical expressions, constants, visual assets, sigil systems,
lore content, white papers, grimoires, READMEs, instructional content, and any
associated intellectual property contained within or referenced by the Obsidian
Protocol organization and its repositories.

**1.3 "Derivative Works"** shall mean any modification, adaptation, translation,
abridgment, compilation, rearrangement, or any other form in which the Materials
are recast, transformed, or adapted, including but not limited to derivative
algorithms, modified engine architectures, and outputs generated from the
Materials as inputs.

**1.4 "Commercial Use"** shall mean any use of the Materials, in whole or in
part, for the purpose of financial gain, including incorporation into products,
services, platforms, or offerings that generate revenue directly or indirectly.

**1.5 "AI/ML Training"** shall mean any process by which the Materials — in whole
or in part, including but not limited to code, mathematical expressions,
documentation, visual assets, or structural patterns — are used as input data,
training data, fine-tuning data, distillation targets, embedding sources, or
prompt engineering references for artificial intelligence, machine learning,
large language models, neural networks, or any analogous computational system.

**1.6 "Authorized Recipient"** shall mean any individual or entity who has
received express written permission from the Licensor under the terms of this
License or a separate commercial licensing agreement.

