**12.2** When the Licensor publishes a new version of this License
(e.g., v1.1, v2.0), the following rules shall apply:

    (a) Materials committed prior to the new version's publication
        remain governed by the version in effect at the time of their
        last commit, unless the Licensor explicitly re-licenses them.

    (b) Materials committed after the new version's publication are
        governed by the new version, unless the commit explicitly
        references a prior version.

    (c) Existing Authorized Recipients who received permissions under
        a prior version retain those permissions under the terms of
        that prior version until such permissions are revoked in
        accordance with Section 6 (Termination).

**12.3** The Licensor may publish updated versions of this License at
any time. Publication shall occur via inclusion in the relevant
repository with an updated version number in the header and a changelog
entry describing material modifications.

**12.4** No amendment, modification, or waiver of any provision of this
License shall be effective unless made in writing and signed by the
